INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (192, 'Varicose veins are simply when the veins of the leg don''t function as they should anymore, and then blood fall back and don''t flow upward as expected, it happens for different reasons in different people, old age is one of the causes. So on the legs the veins will be very obvious and it will bulge out and look like a network of wires joined together.  it is manageable, there are surgical and other forms of mechanical ways to manage it. There are special stockings that can also help with this, kindly request at a big pharmacy around. Best advice is if you or someone you know has varicose veins, let the person go to a hospital, get physically evaluated and the best decision will be made.', 7, 83, 0, null, 0, '2018-10-14 13:43:05', '2019-07-07 16:59:27', null);
INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (193, 'Hello. Varicose veins are big, thickened veins that usually happen just under the skin - most commonly in the legs. We know they are mainly common in a pregnant women, or in some people as they grow older.They can also happen in people who  are overweight- and those who stand/sit for very long periods at a time. Usually the main problems with varicose veins are their appearance and when they cause aching or itching in the legs. In more medically advanced countries there are treatments that can shrink/strip the veins and surgery; otherwise, special compression stockings can be used to treat aching in the legs. People can also use simple emollient cream to prevent dry itchy skin (...contd)', 70, 83, 0, null, 0, '2018-10-14 13:50:26', '2019-07-07 16:59:27', null);
