INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (461, 'This sounds like vaginismus, and could be as a  result of emotional factors, medical factors, or both.

Vaginismus is when the pelvic floor muscles spasms involuntary resulting in painful, difficult and often impossible to have sexual intercourse, to undergo a gynecological exam, or to insert a tampon.

Besides sex, do you also feel pain during tampon insertion or during a gynecological examination? 

Emotional causes of vaginismus include; fear of anticipated pain, anxiety about performance or guilt, traumatic experiences. Insufficient vaginal lubrication, UTI or yeast infection are some physical conditions that might cause vaginismus. 

Diagnosis & treatment is possible, but varies depending on the underlying cause. You will benefit from seeing a doctor who will take a full medical history and carry out a pelvic examination. Treatment modalities include but are not limited to pelvic floor control exercises, counselling and some form of insertion training.', 13, 222, 0, null, 0, '2019-07-09 12:53:17', '2019-07-09 12:53:17', null);
