INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (526, 'Hello, 

Treatment for  PCOS is mostly individualised, because symptoms vary from woman to woman, and oftentimes the treatment is based on the symptoms that you might have and show. Symptoms such irregular period, excessive hair, acne or obesity might show in varying amounts, and treatment often involves lifestyle changes or/and medication depending on the symptoms. 

Due to the high levels of male hormones that prevent the release of an egg in women with PCOS, it might be a little harder to get pregnant. However, a regular physical examination and management with a gynaecologist (or fertility expert) plus lifestyle changes like healthy eating, exercise, monitoring ovulation and timing sexual intercourse plus the use of prescribed medications will improve your chances of having a successful pregnancy.', 13, 254, 0, null, 0, '2019-07-16 20:01:24', '2019-07-16 20:01:24', null);
