INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (529, 'Hello,

Thanks for posting your question. 

Sometimes women experience fluctuations in their menstrual flow and it also varies from one woman to another. Most doctors will tell you the regular flow lasts 3-7 days. However, some will tell you 2 days could be normal. Some factors like stress, weight changes, hormonal issues, contraceptives, medications etc, could affect your cycle.

Are you taking any form of contraceptives, are you on any long term medications? What’s your mental state like and any changes in your weight?

Do well to visit your gynaecologist for a thorough examination.

As regards, getting pregnant, that depends on if you’re producing an egg during your cycle, amongst other factors including your partner’s sperm quality. It takes two to achieve a pregnancy.

