INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (569, 'Your menstrual cycle begins on the first day of your period and continues up to the first day of your next period.
A woman is most fertile during her ovulation period (usually days 12 - 14 before your next period starts).

To answer your question, although it is quite unlikely to get pregnant on the first day of your period, it CAN still happen. Sperm cells can survive for days in the body, thus increasing your chances of getting pregnant especially if you have a short cycle or ovulate early (7 days is early, yes). 

Please note that if you have sex without using contraception, you can get pregnant at any time during your menstrual cycle, even during or just after your period. There''s no "safe" time of the month. Every time you have unprotected sex there are varying risks of becoming pregnant or contracting a sexually transmitted infection. 

