INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (647, 'Hi, with respect to it''s role as a contraceptive, a condom acts like a barrier. It keeps the sperm from getting into the Vagina. Anything that happens that allows that sperm to get into the vagina can result into a pregnancy. So if the condom slips while there is sperm inside and it pours into the Vagina, then pregnancy could occur.  The chances of you getting pregnant if you have sex 3 days after your period are low, but it is very possible, especially if for example you ovulate early, also note that the sperm can survive for up to 5 days after being released into the body. Low risk of pregnancy, but likely. 
