INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (656, 'The process of losing weight can be frustrating, but consistency and persistency is key. 
Some tips to help in your journey are as follows; 

1. Don''t skip breakfast: good options include oats and fruits. 

2. Eat regular meals i.e breakfast, lunch and dinner in moderate portions. 

3. Eat plenty of fruit and veg

4. Get more active, you don’t have to go to gym to be active. Take more walks, skip within your home. YouTube videos are a good place to start.

5. Drink plenty of water, up to 3/4 L spread across the day. 

6. Eat high-fibre foods such as fruit and veg, oats, wholegrain bread, and beans.

7. Don''t start unsustainable diets 

8. Healthy snacks, for when you have to much such as fruit, oat cakes, unsalted or unsweetened popcorn, and dried fruits.

9. Cut down on alcohol and processed sugars, sodas and carbonated drinks 

10. Plan your meals; although it’s difficult to do, planning your breakfast, lunch, dinner and snacks for the week helps you stick to your calorie allowance. You may find it helpful to make a weekly timetable. 

