INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (690, 'Pimples are common, usually harmless at that age. They are often a result of your skin’s oil glands making too much oil which then leads to clogged pores. 

My advice is that you avoid popping, picking at, or touching them as popping may cause scarring. In addition, touching your pimple can transfer oil and bacteria from your hands to your face therefore infecting the pimple and not giving it a chance to heal.

Washing your face regularly, about twice per day, especially when it gets sweaty. This helps to keep oil from building up and clogging your pores. Don''t over-wash or use harsh scrubs. Acne is not caused by dirt. Two gentle washings a day is enough. Too much cleaning can leave skin irritated and dry, triggering glands to produce more oil, increasing the likelihood of pimples.

Stress or hormonal changes can also worsen pimples outbreak. 

Cosmetics and makeup that have a greasy consistency may also clog pores. Water-based products are less likely to cause pimples than oil-based makeup. Use oil-free or noncomedogenic products (those that won''t clog pores) on your face.

Should you have an excessive amount of pimples, you will benefit from speaking to a dermatologist.', 13, 339, 0, null, 0, '2019-08-02 16:25:08', '2019-08-02 16:25:08', null);
INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (691, 'Taste and smell disorders affects a lot of people. Most times, anosmia (loss of sense of smell) is a temporary issue caused by a number of things. In some cases, anosmia may persist and may be a sign of a more serious medical condition that should be reviewed by a doctor. 

Some causes of smell and taste disorders are; nasal congestion from a cold, allergy, sinus infection, nasal polyps, nerve injuries, exposure to toxic chemicals, such as pesticides or solvents, abuse of certain medications etc. 

If the loss of sense of taste and smell doesn’t return within a few days, you will benefit from a physician’s review and management.', 13, 345, 0, null, 0, '2019-08-02 16:50:23', '2019-08-02 16:50:23', null);
