INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (710, 'Hi Anon!

Thanks for your question. Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), you must understand does not have any characteristic symptoms that define it. The virus essentially weakens the body''s immune system causing a variety of manifestations which are also commonly seen in different other conditions. Even after an initial period of symptoms such as fever, sore throat, muscle pain; an infected person may show no other symptoms. This does not mean that the person is now better. The virus is simply quietly further taking over the body. Eventually, HIV if untreated, will become AIDS which has even more severe rather non-specific symptoms.

As the old saying goes, "AIDS no dey show for face". Proper treatment with existing HIV medication will prevent HIV from progressing to AIDS and will enable an individual live a practically normal life.

If you suspect that you may have been exposed to the virus at some, kindly do not hesitate to get tested. HIV is not a death sentence!!

Kind regards!', 207, 357, 0, null, 0, '2019-08-04 06:36:54', '2019-08-04 06:36:54', null);
INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (711, 'Hello. The symptoms of HIV usually occur based on the particular stage of the infection. In the early stages, symptoms may look like malaria or any other ailment. The person could have a high temperature, headache, weakness and just generally feel sick. As the infection progresses, the person will begin to pass watery stool, vomit, lose weight, develop large and painful lymph nodes. 
On further progress of the disease, the person may have a prolonged cough, whitish sores in the mouth and become really sick because the virus has weakened the body''s immune system. These are just few of the many symptoms of HIV infection. 
I encourage you to visit a counseling and testing center to get tested. 

Hope this helps.', 290, 357, 0, null, 0, '2019-08-04 06:41:04', '2019-08-04 06:41:04', null);
