INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (724, 'Lack of blood, or anaemia, is a condition in which the blood doesn''t have enough healthy red blood cells. This leads to reduced oxygen flow to the body''s organs.

There are many types of anaemia with different causes and treatments. 
Iron-deficiency anaemia is the most common and is usually treated with diet changes and iron supplements. 
Other forms of anaemia like the mild anemia that develops during pregnancy are considered normal. However, some other types of anemia may present lifelong health problems.

Symptoms may include fatigue, pale skin, shortness of breath, light-headedness, dizziness or a fast heartbeat. Often times other signs may present, depending on the cause. 

To confirm anaemia, blood tests must be carried out, and also the tests help point to the underlying condition, and then a treatment course or plan may begin.', 13, 364, 0, null, 0, '2019-08-05 14:20:26', '2019-08-05 14:20:26', null);
