INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (763, 'Pinkish discharge is often due to blood mixed with clear or whitish discharge, and may be on account of different conditions.
The timing of the month the discharge occurs— as well as any other symptoms (in this case, itching) can help to identify the underlying cause.

Are you sexually active? Does your partner have any symptoms?  

On account of the associated vaginal itching, I think you might have an STI (sexually transmitted infection). Other symptoms may include; bleeding with sexual intercourse, painful urination, discomfort in your pelvic region, and spotting between periods. 

Without treatment, STIs can spread to the reproductive organs, resulting in Pelvic Inflammatory Disease (PID), and if left untreated, PID can result in chronic pelvic pain and infertility.

