INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (778, 'Depending on the cause of your sore throat, you might not require any treatment. 
However, if there are associated symptoms such as headache, fever, cough etc. that is long lasting then you will need to get it checked out at a doctor’s. 

Regardless of the cause the following techniques are known to bring relief faster;

1. Rest. Get plenty of sleep with minimal talking to rest your throat and reduce irritation. 
2. Drink plenty of fluids. Fluids keep the throat moist and prevent dehydration. Avoid drinks with caffeine and alcohol, as that can lead to dehydration. Warm liquids  are better — soups, tea or warm water with honey etc. 
3. Gargle with saltwater.
4. Consider over the counter lozenges like strepsils or others from the pharmacy. Also consider paracetamol for fever or pain of present. 
5. Go and see your doctor or a community pharmacist if your symptoms don’t reduce in a few days, sore throats can sometimes be a symptom of a more serious illness.', 13, 395, 0, null, 0, '2019-08-13 08:36:15', '2019-08-13 08:36:15', null);
