INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1124, 'Hi, 

There are no effective home remedies for keloids. Also, there isn’t a single treatment plan that is best for all keloids. We have to consider the location, size, and depth of the lesion, the age of the patient and very importantly what treatment has been used in the past and how it was responded to.

There are however numerous treatment plans which includes surgical excision, intralesional steroid injection, radiation therapy, laser therapy, silicone gel sheeting, and pressure therapy. 
Keloids tend to recur after surgical excision as a single treatment, therefore a combination of therapies might be required. 

My advise if that you go see a dermatologist who will examine the lesions and answer those above questions to design a treatment regimen for you. 

Cheers!', 13, 624, 0, null, 0, '2019-10-11 09:15:53', '2019-10-11 09:15:53', null);
