Human Papilloma Virus (the causative agent of genital warts) is transmitted by skin-to-skin contact, and because HPV can infect areas that are not covered by the condom, condoms will not fully protect you against contracting HPV, but condoms do help in reducing the chances of contracting HPV. 

In most cases, for genital warts to be diagnosed, a doctor has to examine and physically check a man''s genital area to see if warts are present, doctors may apply a vinegar solution to help identify warts that aren''t raised and visible. Afterwards, a treatment regimen is discussed and offered. 

