INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1193, 'Hi Temitayo, 

Only tests can confirm pregnancy, and considering your test was positive, you might be pregnant or maybe it a false positive. 

My advise is to repeat the test at a reputable lab for confirmation. 

Also, please note that bleeding or spotting is possible despite being pregnant and this can occur anytime from conception (when the egg is fertilized) to the end of pregnancy. 

Light bleeding during early pregnancy happens due to the attachment of the fertilized egg to the uterine lining, this is known as implantation bleeding. It usually occurs during the time when you are expecting a normal menstrual period, it is generally lighter in comparison to menstrual bleeding. Implantation bleeding is usually light, stops spontaneously and doesn’t need treatment.

Go and confirm your pregnancy status. 

