INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1201, 'Hi, 

A swollen vulva  can be a natural response after rough sex, either because of increased  blood flow to the area or from irritations and friction due to poor lubrication and minimal foreplay prior to intercourse. It could also be from an allergic reaction to the condoms or artificial lubrication used. In most cases it usually resolves within hours and doesn’t have the associated symptoms you listed. 

Swollen vulva is also a common symptom of vaginitis, the inflammation of the vagina, cause from a bacterial, yeast, or viral infection, which is also associated with the other symptoms you have listed. Bacterial vaginosis, STIs and yeast infections are common culprits. 

My advice is that you go to a doctor for physical examination and lab investigations, to confirm cause and provide appropriate treatment depending on the cause. 

Meanwhile, abstain from sex temporarily until tests are carried out to prevent further irritations and worsening. 

