INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1203, 'Hi, 

A change in the duration of your periods can be due to innocuous reasons or something more serious. 

First, let’s rule out the less serious stuff that can change the length of your period, like a change in your schedule or stress, a new birth control or particular medications you just started (including pain killers), excessive exercise or athletic activity, significant weight changes or eating disorder. Also, women notice different kinds of changes in the features or characteristics of their period as they get older. 

Other causes that are considered more serious might include; thyroid disorders, PCOS. However, they usually are accompanied by other symptoms such as acne, or sleep disorders etc. 

How long have you noticed the change? If you haven’t noticed other symptoms, it might be nothing to worry about. However, I would advice that you see your gynaecologist as soon as you can for a routine check up. 

