INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1387, 'Hi Success, 

There are different ways to calculate your due date; 

You can use your last menstrual period (LMP). The number of weeks that have passed since the first day of your last period indicates how old in weeks your pregnancy is. To work out your likely due date, count 280 days (40 weeks) from the first day of your last period.

Using the first ultrasound scan during your antenatal visit, your healthcare provider will also check on fetal growth and monitor other development milestones. Ultrasound scans ALSO provides the most accurate estimate for how many weeks pregnant you are and what your due date will be. This is the MOST RELIABLE method and is particularly useful if you don’t know the date of your last period or if your menstrual cycles are irregular.

Nausea and vomiting are common in pregnancy, especially in the first trimester, usually referred to as morning sickness. In some cases, some pregnant women experience excessive nausea and vomiting that might result in hospitalisation from dehydration. 

Seek medical help if vomiting is so severe or constant that the person can’t keep down fluids or food. The doctor may need to treat you for dehydration and may recommend medication to control vomiting during pregnancy.

