INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1469, 'Hello. Thank you for using Wellvis.

When someone is newly infected with HIV, the person may not show symptoms because the virus has not multiplied to the extent of causing symptoms. If the person is tested, the virus may not be detected. This is called the window period and it usually lasts for about 3 months.

However, subsequently, the person may begin to have fever(rise in body temperature), headaches, diarrhea. Seed like tissues called lymphnodes around the body may get enlarged and painful. The person begins to fall sick easily because the immune system is weak. 

The best way to know if one is infected is via a test. If it''s negative, it should be repeated after 3 months. 

