INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1495, 'Hello, 

Pre-implantation genetic diagnosis (PGD) is a procedure that is performed during in vitro fertilisation (IVF); a form of assisted reproductive technology. 

IVF is the process of fertilisation by extracting eggs from a woman and retrieving a sperm sample from the man and manually combining them to form an embryo (babies develop from embryo). The embryo(s) is then transferred / implanted into the uterus of the mother. 

With PGD, the genetic makeup of each embryo can be determined before being transferred into the uterus of the woman during IVF, therefore almost completely eliminating the risks of bearing a child with sickle cell. Please note that PGD is not 100% accurate. 

Other options are prenatal diagnosis which is usually done while the couple is already pregnant, it involves selective abortion of affected pregnancies. And is significantly cheaper. 

Cost of the procedure differs based on location, centre and health status of the couple. However it is said to be in the millions (or Naira). 

Speak to your primary physician or gynaecologist if you would like to consider this. 

For more information on centres that offer this procedure and appointment bookings, kindly fill this form - https://wellvishealth.typeform.com/to/WAPmQe

Good luck!', 13, 892, 0, null, 0, '2019-12-14 20:55:01', '2019-12-14 20:55:01', null);
INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1496, 'Hi, 

No, getting a Pap smear doesn’t ‘take’ your virginity. 
Virginity has a personal definition, it is not a medical or physical condition. People are commonly considered virgins if they’ve never had penetrative sex. 

Please note that hymens can be stretched open the first time during vaginal sex, sometimes causing some pain or bleeding, this however, is not always the case for everyone. There are other ways that a hymen can be stretched open: riding a bike, doing sports, or putting something in the vagina accidentally to on purpose (like a tampon or during a Pap smear). When the hymen is stretched open, it doesn’t grow back.

Virginity and the presence of a closed hymen are not mutually exclusive, therefore you can’t tell if someone has had sex by the way their hymen looks or feels. Some people are born with hymens that are naturally open, also there are many other activities besides sex can stretch your hymen. 

Cheers!', 13, 893, 0, null, 0, '2019-12-14 21:09:43', '2019-12-14 21:09:43', null);
