INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1504, 'Hi, 

How and when were you diagnosed with diabetes? How and where have you been monitoring your blood sugar? Do you own a glucometer? Do you check before or after a meal? 

Symptoms of diabetes vary and this is often dependent on how elevated your blood sugar is. In many cases when blood sugar is only slightly elevated you might not have any discernible physical symptoms. However, when significantly elevated or long lasting, signs and symptoms of diabetes may include the following; drinking more water, increased urination, high thirst and hunger, weight loss, regular tiredness, eye problems, injuries that doesn’t heal quickly and frequent infections. 

Complications of diabetes develop gradually, and the longer you have uncontrolled blood sugar, the higher the risks of complications. They can be disabling and life-threatening. They include cardiovascular problems such as coronary artery disease, heart attack, stroke and narrowing of arteries (atherosclerosis). Nerve damage which may lead to loss of all feelings and sensations in the limbs and in men, it may lead to erectile dysfunction. Damage to the kidneys, eye etc. may also occur. 

Ideally, a test called Glycated hemoglobin (A1C) test is the best way to know what your diabetic status. You should visit your doctor or a lab and request for this test. You should also repeat a fasting and 2hours post prandial blood sugar at a reputable centre to confirm diagnosis. 

Meanwhile, ensure that you eat healthy foods that are low in fat and calories but higher in fiber. Focus on fruits, vegetables and whole grains. Get more physical activity, of about 30 minutes of moderate physical activity a day such as brisk daily walks or swimming. And don’t forget to aim to lose some body weight to reduce the risk of diabetes.

Should you require an appointment or help finding a doctor or lab in your locality, fill this for and we might be able to help you locate one; https://wellvishealth.typeform.com/to/WAPmQe

Cheers!', 13, 898, 0, null, 0, '2019-12-16 20:56:28', '2019-12-16 20:56:28', null);
