INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1543, 'Sex happens in the vagina, not the urethra. So urinating after sex does not prevent pregnancy
During sex, organisms(some of them may be infectious) are exchanged between partners, and some may get into the urethra. Urinating after sex, may flush the urethra, as an attempt to remove organisms, but don''t rely on it. Practice safe sex.

After sex, semen flows back out of the vagina(seminal effluvium). This is expected and normal, as the vagina does not have a lid. Don''t be alarmed by it, and don''t get scammed by quacks who wants to steal money from you in the name of treatments.

A man releases between 50 - 250 million sperms per milliliter of sperm, upon ejaculation. Only 1 is needed to fertilise the female''s ovum(egg). So, unless your partner''s semen or sperms have a problem, you don''t have a problem

However, if your partner and you have been having adequate sexual intercourse, which means
1. Peno-vaginal sex,
2. at least 3 times per week on alternate days,
