INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (1684, 'Hello there and thanks for using Wellvis.

First of all, I hope you’re feeling much better following your recent surgery.

Regarding sexual activity, most surgeons recommend waiting a minimum of 4-6 weeks after surgery before having intercourse. This allows for the pain to subside and for the surgical wound to heal better. There are other factors involved depending on the reason for the surgery.

However, when you do resume sexual intercourse, it is recommended to wait for at least 6 months before getting pregnant (if you are trying to).

Your follow-up checks with your gynaecologist is very important and you should report any worrying symptoms like a high fever, nausea or vomiting, severe pain, bleeding from the surgical site, chest or breathing issues, abnormal vaginal discharge etc.

Also, moderate walking is helpful in your healing process and eating healthy too with high fibre, to avoid constipation.

Once again, thanks for using Wellvis and in case you want a more personalised experience, we have the live chat function which connects you to one of our verified doctors at a very reasonable fee. 

