INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (2098, 'I’m sorry Mr Olayiwola for your symptoms. What you actually have is glare. 
Glare is the loss of visual discomfort or performance which occurs when the intensity of light in the visual field (intensity of light entering the eyes) is greater than the intensity of light to which the eyes are adapted. Simply put, glare occurs when too much light enters your eye and interferes with your eye''s ability to manage it. 
Common eye problems that can cause glare include;
 👉Recent corrective eye surgery like cataract surgery
👉Refractive eye diseases such as:
✝️Nearsightedness (difficulty seeing things far away)
✝️Farsightedness (trouble perceiving things nearby)
✝️Presbyopia (difficulty reading small prints due to aging)
✝️Astigmatism (blurry vision due to the irregular shape of the eye)

If the history of recent eye surgery is ruled, you may be having one or more of these refractive errors mentioned above. So you will require better than just dark glasses.  You will need a medicated glasses with photochromic lenses with/without anti-reflex.
I will suggest you book an appointment with a nearby ophthalmologist for proper examination and prompt treatment.

I wish you all the best.', 581, 1313, 1, '2020-05-20 19:19:58', 0, '2020-05-20 19:15:15', '2020-05-20 19:19:58', null);
