This means that no vaginal discharge should be taken to be ordinary until the doctor says so.

Each cause of vaginal discharge can be differentiated by it''s distinctive colour or smell. A note of it''s consistency should also be noted.

However the description you gave of the vaginal discharge (with respect to it''s colour and odour) shows it is most likely an abnormal vaginal discharge.

