Did he use a common blade at the barber’s shop? Is this the first time it’s happening? Have you noticed any bumps on his head?

What you have described sounds like folliculitis, sometimes called Barber’s itch. It is an infection of the hair follicles usually from poorly sterilised shaving equipment. The infection could be from bacteria, fungi or viruses in some cases. It normally resolves in about two weeks with just home management. However if poorly treated, could have complications.

I’ll recommend you wash his head and put a warm moist cloth or towel over it after that. Depending on the causative organism, you can apply an antibacterial or antifungal cream or ointment.

