INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (2247, 'Hello there!
Also known as mouth odor,halitosis could be an embarassing condition to the sufferer and the diagnosis can be quite tricky to the dentist.It can be classified into, True halitosis  and Psychogenic halitosis(false halitosis in which the person just feels he has mouth odor even when nobody has ever told him his mouth was smelling).
Having said that,there are  a couple of likely causes of true halitosis and these determine the chronicity of the condition.Some of the possible causes include:
1.Poor oral hygiene-A heavy presence of plaque and calculus(yellowish to dark colored deposits on the teeth) in the mouth will cause mouth odor.Also, non-brushing or improper brushing of the tongue is a major cause of halitosis.The tongue is the largest reservoir of food debris in the mouth hence, not brushing the tongue is like not brushing at all.
2.Diets: Frequent concsumption of onions,garlic,beans and other food which produce Volatile sulphur compounds(VSC).These VSCs play a major role in diet-asociated halitosis.
3.Systemic diseases like Chronic Kidney disease,Gastroesophageal reflux disorders(GERD) can also cause halitosis.
Also,halitosis is associated with eating disorders like Bulimia nervosa, where people engage in acts of  intentionally inducing vomitting of food ingested.Besides some people engage in the habit of regurgitating ingested food and this could also lead to mouth odor.

Based on all I  have stated above,the best way to diagnose halitosis would be for you to visit a dentist.The dentist will have to examine your mouth thoroughly and evaluate the possible causes of the halitosis in your case.
Have you ever had scaling and polishing ? It is very possible the chronic halitosis in your case is because you have never visited the dentist.Scaling and polishing is a procedure which is meant to be done every six months  at least,and this is a way to clear the "cobwebs" in our mouths(the plaque and calculus which I mentioned earlier).
Best regards', 15, 1419, 0, null, 0, '2020-06-30 21:52:48', '2020-06-30 21:52:48', null);
