The ophthalmologist therefore has to assess the baby''s vision to see if it''s reduced or not, his eye movements to assess the strength of the eye muscles and to even check the inside of the eye (by use of an instrument)
Now the treatment will depend on what''s discovered. If there is an underlying disease causing the squint, whether inside the eye or not, it is the disease that will be treated. If he has decreased vision in the affected eye(s), that will be corrected too. There is also role for surgery, which aims to improve cosmetic appearance and to tighten or loosen the eye muscles. 
