INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (2347, 'Hello,

Bilateral breasts swelling with associated nipple discharge; How long have you noticed the swelling? Is it permanent or it comes and goes? What is the colour and consistency of the discharge? Are you pregnant or recently pregnant? Does it come out on its own, or do you have to squeeze the nipple for it to come out? Are you in any medications? Are there any physical changes besides the swelling, in your breasts; change in the way your nipple or the skin of the breasts look? 

Regarding the pain; hormones are the number one suspects when it comes to breast pain, especially if it occurs three to five days prior to your period. Is there any history of trauma to the breasts?

The other listed symptoms may be associated with the breast symptoms or not, however, answers to the above listed questions can provide guidance towards reaching a cause. 
You can have a private chat with a doctor here for advice on what to do next and how to treat or prevent the pains in the future. 

