INSERT INTO ebdb.thread_comments (id, content, user_id, thread_id, is_retrieved, retrieved_at, is_answer, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) VALUES (2548, 'Hello, 

Fallopian tubes connect the ovaries and the uterus, and every month during ovulation, the egg travels from the ovaries to the uterus via the tubes. Therefore, once these tubes are blocked, the chances of pregnancy are slimmer. 

The most common cause of blocked fallopian tubes is PID, others include; 	previous ectopic pregnancy, endometriosis etc. Also, tubes can be blocked due to tubal ligation, a procedure whereby tubes are medically tied. 

Blocked tubes are usually diagnosed with a specialized x-ray called a hysterosalpingogram (HSG). 

Treatment options vary and are dependent on the degree of blockage or if both tubes are affected. Options include; surgery, IVF or reversal of ligation depending on the results of examinations.', 13, 1641, 0, null, 0, '2020-09-13 08:38:32', '2020-09-13 08:38:32', null);
